result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordan J Schauz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).
  • OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Jordan J Schauz in court with attorney Katie Beth Bricco.  Jayne Davis Dewire appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1 & 2.  Court finds defendant guilty.

Court orders the following: 
Count 1:
- Total sentence: Withheld sentence; 2 years Probation. 
- Alcohol Assessment
- Fine totaling: $268.00 to be paid as a Condition Probation
- DNA Surcharge of $250.00; append to fine
- Conditions of Probation: Maintain absolute sobriety.  Prescriptions may only be used in the amounts prescribed to him by his physician.  Random drug screenings Submit to an AODA assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Follow thru with any treatment/counseling recommended by Agent. DNA Sample if not yet provided.
**Court grants expungement if the defendant successfully completes probation.**

Court orders the following: 
Count 2:
- Total sentence: 90 days Jail with Huber (62 days credit)
- 24 months Drivers License Revocation. 
- 24 months Ignition Interlock on every vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant
- Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel meeting while on Extended Supervision
- Alcohol Assessment
- Fine totaling: $1494.00 to be paid as a Condition Probation on count 1; alternate 29 days jail; consecutive
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Waukesha Police Department; append to fine.

Defendant was remanded to the custody of the Sheriff to commence the sentence.
